inst:effect_3048 a evid:EffectSize ;
    rdfs:label "effect_3048" ;
    evid:hasDependentVariable inst:measure_meas_3037 ;
    evid:hasEffectLevel "team"^^xsd:string ;
    evid:hasEffectSizeValue "-0.054"^^xsd:float ;
    evid:hasIndependentVariable inst:measure_meas_3036 ;
    evid:hasNotes "To better understand these results, we reran this model with a factorized version of performance to extract the estimates for each performance group. As can be seen in Fig. 2, as performance increases, the shape of the quadratic trend is signi cantly shallowed for the middle performing (β=−0.045, SE= 0.012, p < .001) and the high performing groups (β=−0.054, SE = 0.013, p < .001), when com- pared to the lowest performing group. That is, while it appears during the rst and last periods coherences is approximately the same for all groups, in the highest performing group, the average coherence over time exhibits quite a shallow quadratic trend with the highest average values. Thus, coherence for the top performing teams, while showing a small decrease, remains relatively stable over time. By contrast, the low performing group exhibited a pattern of coherence that decreases from the rst until the midpoint, before rising back again to approximately its original level. Thus, the way that the movement coordination changes over the duration of the task (i.e., remain stable versus de- creases sharply) is diagnostic of performance on this collaborative task.; high performing groups, when compared to the lowest performing group."^^xsd:string ;
    evid:hasSE "0.013"^^xsd:float ;
    evid:hasSignificanceCategory "Significantly negative"^^xsd:string ;
    evid:usesEffectSizeMetric "regression beta"^^xsd:string .

