    evid:hasNotes "Observer-rated behavioral coordination associated with dyadic neural synchrony.; Undergraduate dyads; correlational; most of the reported ANOVAs/χ² are about task-type and distribution/entropy. The multiple tests (per task, electrode, band, window, etc.) are different contrasts/operationalizations of that same effect—not new effects. Task Type × Distribution: χ²(2) = 8.01, p = .02 (significant); Communication Code × Distribution: χ²(4) = 8.79, p = .07 (ns); Fz electrode, alpha band: p = .002 (NEO < Minecraft)._x000D_ Fz electrode, beta band: p = .02 (NEO < Minecraft)._x000D_ No other Task Type main effects were significant; the 2×2×2 mixed ANOVA interaction was reported as not depending on Interaction (no specific p given)"^^xsd:string ;
