inst:measure_meas_029 a meas:Measure ;
    rdfs:label "Cardiac IBI coupling (CC)" ;
    meas:hasDescription """Two disposable electrodes were placed on the sternum (at the maxilla and xiphoid process) of each participant to record ECG at 480 Hz using two wireless radio transmitters (Cleveland Medical Devices Inc., BioRadio, model BR150 â€“900)
interfaced with custom software that was developed by the Air Force Research Laboratory (AFRL) to identify and record IBIs (defined as the time, in milliseconds, between successive R-peaks in a continuous stream of recorded ECG). (Cross-correlation)""",
        "Two disposable electrodes were placed on the sternum (at the maxilla and xiphoid process) of each participant to record ECG at 480 Hz using two wireless radio transmitters (Cleveland Medical Devices Inc., BioRadio, model BR150 –900)_x000D_ interfaced with custom software that was developed by the Air Force Research Laboratory (AFRL) to identify and record IBIs (defined as the time, in milliseconds, between successive R-peaks in a continuous stream of recorded ECG). (Cross-correlation)" ;
    meas:hasLevelOfAnalysis inst:level_individual_team ;
    meas:hasName "Cardiac IBI coupling (CC)" ;
    meas:includesModality inst:modality_physiology_cardiac_ibi ;
    meas:measuresConstruct inst:construct_workload ;
    meas:usesAnalyticTechnique inst:tech_dsa_cross_recurrence_quantification_analysis_crqa,
        inst:tech_dsa_crqa_cross_recurrence_quantification_analysis .

inst:measure_meas_030 a meas:Measure ;
    rdfs:label "Cardiac IBI coupling (%REC)" ;
    meas:hasDescription """Two disposable electrodes were placed on the sternum (at the maxilla and xiphoid process) of each participant to record ECG at 480 Hz using two wireless radio transmitters (Cleveland Medical Devices Inc., BioRadio, model BR150 â€“900)
interfaced with custom software that was developed by the Air Force Research Laboratory (AFRL) to identify and record IBIs (defined as the time, in milliseconds, between successive R-peaks in a continuous stream of recorded ECG). (%RECâ€”the relative number of matching data point sequences between two time series compared with the total matches possible)""",
        "Two disposable electrodes were placed on the sternum (at the maxilla and xiphoid process) of each participant to record ECG at 480 Hz using two wireless radio transmitters (Cleveland Medical Devices Inc., BioRadio, model BR150 –900)_x000D_ interfaced with custom software that was developed by the Air Force Research Laboratory (AFRL) to identify and record IBIs (defined as the time, in milliseconds, between successive R-peaks in a continuous stream of recorded ECG). (%REC—the relative number of matching data point sequences between two time series compared with the total matches possible)" ;
    meas:hasLevelOfAnalysis inst:level_individual_team ;
    meas:hasName "Cardiac IBI coupling (%REC)" ;
    meas:includesModality inst:modality_physiology_cardiac_ibi ;
    meas:measuresConstruct inst:construct_workload ;
    meas:usesAnalyticTechnique inst:tech_dsa_cross_recurrence_quantification_analysis_crqa,
        inst:tech_dsa_crqa_cross_recurrence_quantification_analysis .

inst:measure_meas_031 a meas:Measure ;
    rdfs:label "Cardiac IBI coupling (CFEn)" ;
    meas:hasDescription """Two disposable electrodes were placed on the sternum (at the maxilla and xiphoid process) of each participant to record ECG at 480 Hz using two wireless radio transmitters (Cleveland Medical Devices Inc., BioRadio, model BR150 â€“900)
interfaced with custom software that was developed by the Air Force Research Laboratory (AFRL) to identify and record IBIs (defined as the time, in milliseconds, between successive R-peaks in a continuous stream of recorded ECG). (CFEn = cross-fuzzy entropy)""",
        "Two disposable electrodes were placed on the sternum (at the maxilla and xiphoid process) of each participant to record ECG at 480 Hz using two wireless radio transmitters (Cleveland Medical Devices Inc., BioRadio, model BR150 –900)_x000D_ interfaced with custom software that was developed by the Air Force Research Laboratory (AFRL) to identify and record IBIs (defined as the time, in milliseconds, between successive R-peaks in a continuous stream of recorded ECG). (CFEn = cross-fuzzy entropy)" ;
    meas:hasLevelOfAnalysis inst:level_individual_team ;
    meas:hasName "Cardiac IBI coupling (CFEn)" ;
    meas:includesModality inst:modality_physiology_cardiac_ibi ;
    meas:measuresConstruct inst:construct_workload ;
    meas:usesAnalyticTechnique inst:tech_dsa_cross_recurrence_quantification_analysis_crqa,
